summary: This document is a subpoena from the Epstein case to Fifth Third Bank requesting comprehensive financial records for all open and closed accounts related to specified individuals and entities. It demands transaction files, identification documents, wire transfers, safe deposit records, loan applications, online banking information, and all correspondence from account inception to present.

locations.address: 5050 Kingsley Drive Mail Drop 1MOC2Q Cincinnati, OH 45263

keyFacts: A comprehensive subpoena was issued to Fifth Third Bank demanding extensive financial records related to the Epstein investigation.
The subpoena requests records for 'all open and closed accounts' pertaining to specified individuals and entities, indicating a broad financial investigation.
Requested materials include transaction files, identification documents, wire transfers, safe deposit records, loan applications, and online banking information.
The subpoena specifically demands 'any and all correspondence, electronic or otherwise' including emails and text messages referencing financial interests.
The document reference EFTA00083691 suggests this is part of a larger set of financial investigation documents in the Epstein case.
